      "writtenOn": "2026-07-07T12:27:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I would like the defaults to be some kind of sane defaults.  I don\u0027t understand why \"enabled\u003dfalse\" is a good default for us.  Shouldn\u0027t we make the default \"widely useful and available\"?\n\nMy general feeling is that people should not have to \"provision\" a system to make it do something expected.  Having to do provisioning means that after a factory reset (or file system corruption) the system is now in an undesired state.",
      "revId": "6b17f676c47ce3953befbd5430fec0303e808a07",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
